1 IC 35-45-9, or IC 35-46-10, the person may bring a civil action against
2 the person who caused the loss for the following:
3 (1) An amount not to exceed three (3) times:
4 (A) the actual damages of the person suffering the loss, in the
5 case of a liability that is not covered by IC 24-4.6-5; or
6 (B) the total pump price of the motor fuel received, in the case
7 of a liability that is covered by IC 24-4.6-5.
8 (2) The costs of the action.
9 (3) A reasonable attorney's fee.
10 (4) Actual travel expenses that are not otherwise reimbursed
11 under subdivisions (1) through (3) and are incurred by the person
12 suffering loss to:
13 (A) have the person suffering loss or an employee or agent of
14 that person file papers and attend court proceedings related to
15 the recovery of a judgment under this chapter; or
16 (B) provide witnesses to testify in court proceedings related to
17 the recovery of a judgment under this chapter.
18 (5) A reasonable amount to compensate the person suffering loss
19 for time used to:
20 (A) file papers and attend court proceedings related to the
21 recovery of a judgment under this chapter; or
22 (B) travel to and from activities described in clause (A).
23 (6) Actual direct and indirect expenses incurred by the person
24 suffering loss to compensate employees and agents for time used
25 to:
26 (A) file papers and attend court proceedings related to the
27 recovery of a judgment under this chapter; or
28 (B) travel to and from activities described in clause (A).
29 (7) All other reasonable costs of collection.
